The only thing I find a little hard to wrap my head around, is the notion that the alcohol it produces can be more intoxicating. Alcohol is alcohol; other than being more or less concentrated in the liquid as compared to other components(water, sugar, etc). Unless there are other additional excressions that cause side effect intoxications outside of normal alcohol consumption. Normal yeast dies at a concentration maximum of approx 18%. So I would revise to either make the claim that it can survive/tolerate alcohol concentrations up to 36% which would be the equivalent of being twice as strong. The other thing that might be interesting is to have this SCP synthesize a mild form of psilocybin it uses to induce subjects to bring it the desired grains and fruits via subtle telepathic suggestion. This would also explain the additional intoxicating effects of the alcohol produced and spores containing similar compounds could explain the intoxicating effects of the  excreted as well







